    "markdown": "---\ntitle: Plotting\naliases:\n  - plotting.html\nauthor: Marie-Hélène Burle\n---\n\n:::{.def}\n\nThis section demos briefly the very basics of plotting in Julia.\n\nYou will learn a lot more about plotting in the next section.\n\n:::\n\n## Plotting in the REPL\n\nIt can be convenient to plot directly in the REPL (for instance when using SSH).\n\n::: {#2 .cell execution_count=1}\n``` {.julia .cell-code}\nusing UnicodePlots\nhistogram(randn(1000), nbins=40)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=1}\n\n::: {.ansi-escaped-output}\n```{=html}\n<pre>                <span class=\"ansi-bright-black-fg\">┌                                        ┐</span> \n   [-3.6, -3.4) <span class=\"ansi-bright-black-fg\">┤</span><span class=\"ansi-green-fg\">▍</span> 1                                     <span class=\"ansi-bright-black-fg\"> </span> \n   [-3.4, -3.2) <span class=\"ansi-bright-black-fg\">┤</span><span class=\"ansi-green-fg\"> </span> 0                                     <span class=\"ansi-bright-black-fg\"> </span> \n   [-3.2, -3.0) <span class=\"ansi-bright-black-fg\">┤</span><span class=\"ansi-green-fg\">█</span><span class=\"ansi-green-fg\">▏</span> 3                                    <span class=\"ansi-bright-black-fg\"> </span> \n   [-3.0, -2.8) <span class=\"ansi-bright-black-fg\">┤</span><span class=\"ansi-green-fg\">▋</span> 2                                     <span class=\"ansi-bright-black-fg\"> </span> \n   [-2.8, -2.6) <span class=\"ansi-bright-black-fg\">┤</span><span class=\"ansi-green-fg\">█</span><span class=\"ansi-green-fg\">▏</span> 3                                    <span class=\"ansi-bright-black-fg\"> </span> \n   [-2.6, -2.4) <span class=\"ansi-bright-black-fg\">┤</span><span class=\"ansi-green-fg\">▋</span> 2                                     <span class=\"ansi-bright-black-fg\"> </span> \n   [-2.4, -2.2) <span class=\"ansi-bright-black-fg\">┤</span><span class=\"ansi-green-fg\">▍</span> 1           